1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with coding and communication, which are core topics in information theory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the design of practical codes for computing functions, which involves algorithmic considerations. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper considers the case when the exact function is not known, but some approximate function or a class to which the function belongs is known, which is a common scenario in machine learning. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with communication between agents, which can be modeled as a network. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the minimum rate for the problem, which can be seen as a measure of computational complexity.
